solution:
The cylinder has volume $\pi (12)^2 (24)$ cubic cm.  Each cone has volume $(1/3)\pi (12)^2(12)$ cubic cm.  Hence the volume of the space in the cylinder not occupied by the cones is  \begin{align*}
\pi (12)^2 (24) - (2)(1/3)\pi (12)^2(12) &= 12^3\pi(2-2/3)\\
&=12^3\pi(4/3)\\
&=\boxed{2304\pi} \text{ cubic cm}.
\end{align*}

